.TH "rave_sp_eeprom_io" 9 "rave_sp_eeprom_io" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rave_sp_eeprom_io \- Low-level part of EEPROM page access
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rave_sp_eeprom_io
.BI "(struct rave_sp_eeprom *eeprom "  ","
.BI "enum rave_sp_eeprom_access_type type "  ","
.BI "u16 idx "  ","
.BI "struct rave_sp_eeprom_page *page "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "eeprom" 12
EEPROM device to write to
.IP "type" 12
EEPROM access type (read or write)
.IP "idx" 12
number of the EEPROM page
.IP "page" 12
Data to write or buffer to store result (via page->data)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function does all of the low-level work required to perform a
EEPROM access. This includes formatting correct command payload,
sending it and checking received results.

Returns zero in case of success or negative error code in
case of failure.
